headline: Trump Visits Iowa While 2028 Republicans Wait for Their Chance

headline: That Sound You Hear Is Rate-Cut Odds Collapsing: Reactions to the Jobs Report
summary: Kevin Gordon, senior investment strategist at Charles Schwab, said the jobs report will wash out expectations of an interest-rate cut this month—something that can be seen in CME Group data. Guy Berger, senior fellow at the Burning Glass Institute, called the report fairly positive, saying it was "better than moderate pessimists like myself were expecting.

headline: Traders Bet on Fewer Rate Cuts After Solid Jobs Report
summary: Traders have significantly dialed back bets on interest-rate cuts after Thursday’s stronger-than-expected jobs report.    Interest-rate futures showed the chances of a cut in July fell to 5% from 24% Wednesday, according to CME Group data.
